<TITLE> BJP blames Congress for price rises in India </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW DELHI, Wed Apr 15, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The following is a snapshot of recent developments in India's general election campaign. (The sources are mentioned in brackets). The Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) blamed the Congress-led ruling coalition for rising prices of essential commodities, despite government claims that inflation was going down. (The Times of India) Congress leader Rahul Gandhi said Prime Minister Manmohan Singh was not weak as the political opposition was making out to be in their election speeches. Gandhi, son of former Prime Minister Rajiv Gandhi, said Singh was the pride of the country. (The Times of India) The Election Commission of India has issued a notice to Lalu Prasad Yadav, leader of the Rashtriya Janata Dal, a powerful regional party from Bihar, for violating election rules and landing a chopper inside a school playground. (Hindustan Times) J. Jayalalithaa, head of the regional All India Anna Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam (AIADMK) in Tamil Nadu, said her party was keeping all post-poll options open, and would negotiate with the frontrunner after election results were out. (The Times of I
